Biography
 
Congratulations! You are now the proud owner of an Arylle. To ensure that you receive the full benefits of your mini-tank, please follow the instruction manual exactly. Doing otherwise could be hazardous to your health as well as others in the vicinity.

Please note: the Arylle is exceptionally difficult to deal with. If you are easily frightened, sensitive, noisy, overbearing, needy, or take rejection badly - you may be dissatisfied with the unit.

Programming
When you first receive your Arylle unit she will be cranky and anti-social. This is not a programming malfunction. If you wanted something nicer you should have bought a priest. Your Arylle is made for fighting, and has many useful functions:
  • Defender: Are you tired of being 1 rounded by heavy hitters? Then the Arylle is for you. She is formidable fighter unit with six different attacks that can be used for exterminating NPCs with very low strain on your healers. The Arylle unit works best with a Teiris unit.
  • Chauffer: Need to get somewhere safely and quickly? The Arylle unit will make sure you arrive on-time and unharmed. If there are other people at your destination, it is recommended that you leave your Arylle outside for everyone's safety.
  • Cleaning House (not to be confused with housework): Maybe you’re an anti-social type too, and just want to be left alone. Your Arylle has the unique ability to clear an entire house of all life forms (except yourself) with a simple glare and a few words.
  • Master Artisan: Your Arylle is a trade skilling master and can assist with difficult combines. To prevent any safety hazards, you should do the tedious sub-combines yourself.

Settings:
  • Civil (default): Please note that civil does not mean nice, it means tolerant (doesn’t go out of her way to injure you, your siblings, other units, etc.)
  • Angry: Attacks will be verbal. Such as but not limited to: insults and death threats.
  • Enraged: Attacks will be physical, and will cause bodily harm and destruction.
  • Content: Your Arylle unit’s Content mode is difficult to activate. Give her a Vah'shir that will stand by quietly while she squeezes it's paw pads.

Care:
  • Feeding: Your Arylle is a master chef and will not eat anything you make, but will expect you to keep ingredients on hand.
  • Cleaning: Your Arylle is self-cleaning. Should she become excessively dirty from battle, do not attempt to wash her yourself or suggest that cleaning is needed. Send her on a quest to an underwater zone and hope for the best.
  • Maintenance: Your Arylle requires AAs and new gear every expansion. Failure to provide the needed maintenance will result in performance decline and changes the default mode from civil to angry.

FAQs:
Q: My Arylle will not stop glaring at me. How do I make her act differently?
A: Even in the default (civil) setting glaring is normal and part of the programming. However, if she seems to be glaring more than usual - you may simply be too talkative for her liking. Arylle units always glare at things they don’t like. She doesn’t have a problem, it’s probably you.

Q: My Arylle will not eat the Misty Thicket Picnics I made her, why is this?
A: Two reasons
  1. you made it, and
  2. it's a picnic - what do you expect? Why don't you go write in your diary and watch Titanic while you are at it you big pansy.

Q: Why is my Arylle taking excessive damage lately?
A: It's mostly likely your fault. From a safe distance - inspect your Arylle to ensure the proper maintenance has been completed.
